comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T04:57:08.891Z",codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625,"Duplicate check: status-all package/profile searches found closed package platform and exemplar work, while pm package catalog currently has no baseline/profile/archetype package."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T07:28:54.194Z",claude-code-agent,"ENABLING PRIMITIVE SHIPPED (in the pm-v37g/pm-bhmk profiles PR): SDK now exports defineProjectProfile (typed identity builder for ProjectProfileDefinition), BUILTIN_PROFILES, PROFILE_NAMES, resolveProfile, listProfiles, normalizeProfileName, and the pure planProfileApplication + ProfileApplicationPlan/ProfileCurrentState types. The three built-in archetypes (agile/ops/research) dogfood the model. REMAINING follow-up scope for this item: build an installable first-party package (e.g. pm-baseline-profile) that defines a profile via defineProjectProfile AND make it applicable from a package. Gap: profile apply orchestration (lock/write/hooks/templates) lives in cli/commands/profile.ts and is NOT yet SDK-exported, and `pm profile apply` only resolves BUILTIN_PROFILES — there is no external-profile registration path yet. So pm-a7o4 needs either (a) an SDK applyProfile orchestration export + an extension capability to register profiles into the `pm profile` resolver, or (b) the package ships a thin command that calls planProfileApplication + writes. Keep open, blocked-by pm-v37g (now satisfied for the primitive half)."
body: "## Implementation plan (claude-code-agent, 2026-06-25)\n\n**Deliverable:** new first-party package `packages/pm-kanban` — an installable exemplar that ships a complete **Kanban continuous-flow archetype/profile** built on public SDK primitives only. Closes the last open child of epic pm-ugqx.\n\n**Why a new archetype (not re-export of agile/ops/research):** a redistributable 4th archetype proves the \"ship a complete project-management archetype as a pm package\" pattern end-to-end, distinct from the three core-baked profiles. Kanban (flow/WIP) is broadly useful and complements the sprint-based `agile` profile.\n\n**Authoring pattern (decided after recon):** mirror `pm-command-kit` (single `index.ts`, `import type` only from `@unbrained/pm-cli/sdk`, synchronous hand-written `activate`). NOT the runtime-loader pattern — no runtime SDK *values* are needed at activation, so we avoid `runtime.ts`/`runtime-loader.ts`/`gen-package-runtime-loaders` drift. This is exactly what the `pm package init --capability schema` scaffold documents, so the exemplar matches the scaffold output (pedagogically ideal).\n\n**Package contents:**\n- Item type `Card` (folder `cards`, alias `kanban-card`) via `api.registerItemTypes`.\n- Fields `wip_limit` (number), `class_of_service` (string), `blocked_reason` (string) via `api.registerItemFields` — verified none shadow BUILTIN_FIELD_KEYS.\n- No-op migration `kanban-profile-init` via `api.registerMigration` (demonstrates schema evolution).\n- Manifest: `capabilities:[\"schema\"]`, **OMIT `activation.commands`** (global schema types must load under the conservative tier so `pm create Card` works), `sandbox_profile:\"strict\"`, all permissions false.\n- Exported `kanbanProfile: ProjectProfileDefinition` = complete archetype spec (types/statuses[`doing`,`verifying`]/fields/Card workflow/config[bm25,max=30]/`card` template/package recs) — dogfoods `defineProjectProfile`/`planProfileApplication`.\n\n**\"Applies the profile\" semantics:** install → schema (Card+fields) live globally → `pm create Card` creates sample items. The non-schema dimensions (statuses/config/templates) are the profile spec a consumer stages via `pm profile`-style apply; README documents this and the test exercises `planProfileApplication(kanbanProfile, …)`.\n\n**Files added:** `packages/pm-kanban/{package.json,README.md,extensions/kanban/{index.ts,manifest.json}}`, `tests/unit/packages/kanban-extension.spec.ts` (100% coverage of index.ts via `createExtensionTestHarness` + `assertRegisteredItemType/Field/Migration` + `runRegisteredMigrationForTest` + `planProfileApplication`).\n\n**Files updated:** `tests/unit/packages/package-manifest.spec.ts` (3 hardcoded package lists + docs/examples loop), `docs/EXTENSIONS.md` (both bundled-package lists), `docs/SDK.md` (profile-package reference), `scripts/dogfood-package-first.mjs` (add `kanban` to the catalog-alias assertion loop).\n\n**Verification:** repo `pnpm typecheck` + 100/100/100/100 coverage + docstring gate; manual temp-dir dogfood (`pm install packages/pm-kanban`, `pm package doctor`, `pm schema list`, `pm create Card`, `pm profile`-style staging).\n\n## Correction (claude-code-agent, 2026-06-25)\n\nThe third flow field shipped as **`impediment`** (string), NOT `blocked_reason` as stated in the implementation-plan note above. `blocked_reason` is a reserved item-metadata key (FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER), so `pm create --type Card` rejected it during the dogfood; renamed to the Kanban-domain term `impediment`. Final fields: `wip_limit` (number), `class_of_service` (string), `impediment` (string)."
